Site Crit - Rieview


18 Aug 2020 04:14






This is well, that's where it sort of falls apart for me.

There are two really big issues here. The first is that I'm really not sure why any of this is happening? Brigham gives up the ghost immediately and I don't know why. I also don't know why he did this. And not in a  kind of way.

It doesn't feel like a natural character consequence so much as  but then he kills her? Weird.

The second issue relates to the magic. I have no idea why this is happening. Again, he casts a spell, it doesn't entirely work, but then also it has this secondary fear causing effect. But there's no throughline, and the mention of  just raises more questions than it answers - what are these? What are the rules? Why did they do this?

The pieces are all here, but the throughline isn't quite, in a way that unfortunately detracts from the piece.

SoullessSingularity if there's an issue





